1
00:00:00,900 --> 00:00:02,567
<i>Peter disappeared
from Hotel 88.</i>

2
00:00:02,700 --> 00:00:03,933
<i> He was last seen there.</i>

3
00:00:04,067 --> 00:00:05,467
<i> We still haven't seen him.</i>

4
00:00:05,600 --> 00:00:07,533
<i>But our people
won't stop looking.</i>

5
00:00:07,667 --> 00:00:09,033
<i> Is Edward your boyfriend?</i>

6
00:00:09,167 --> 00:00:12,833
<i>No. But if you're asking
if he's courting me...</i>

7
00:00:12,967 --> 00:00:14,233
<i> then yes.</i>

8
00:00:15,433 --> 00:00:17,467
<i>- Come with me.
- Where are we going?</i>

9
00:00:17,600 --> 00:00:19,433
<i>We're not going to talk
about the investors, so...</i>

10
00:00:19,567 --> 00:00:20,400
<i> Let's go.</i>

11
00:00:20,533 --> 00:00:21,867
<i>I saw Uncle Andy talking
on the phone.</i>

12
00:00:22,000 --> 00:00:23,400
<i> I heard his voice.</i>

13
00:00:23,533 --> 00:00:24,567
<i> I know it was him.</i>

14
00:00:24,700 --> 00:00:26,300
<i> Your life is in danger!</i>

15
00:00:29,433 --> 00:00:31,767
- [LEON] Sir Henri.
- Oh, Mr. Almazan.

16
00:00:32,533 --> 00:00:34,000
Do you have anything to report?

17
00:00:34,167 --> 00:00:35,267
[GLOOMY MUSIC PLAYING]

18
00:00:35,400 --> 00:00:37,433
[SIGHING]

19
00:00:38,700 --> 00:00:40,333
Can I talk to Roi?

20
00:00:48,767 --> 00:00:50,033
Are you an addict, Leon?

21
00:00:50,167 --> 00:00:51,100
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

22
00:00:51,233 --> 00:00:53,100
I am not an addict.

23
00:00:54,033 --> 00:00:55,933
I'm just telling you
what I believe.

24
00:00:56,067 --> 00:00:57,433
[DOOR CREAKING]

25
00:01:02,400 --> 00:01:03,367
[SNICKERS]

26
00:01:03,500 --> 00:01:05,833
You locked me up,

27
00:01:06,567 --> 00:01:09,433
and now you're telling me
that you think...

28
00:01:09,967 --> 00:01:12,233
I didn't kill your fathers?

29
00:01:15,300 --> 00:01:22,333
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

30
00:02:15,067 --> 00:02:17,600
You're not in prison
for killing them.

31
00:02:18,933 --> 00:02:20,433
Let me remind you...

32
00:02:22,267 --> 00:02:23,833
of what you did to Jade.

33
00:02:32,667 --> 00:02:33,833
I learned something.

34
00:02:36,700 --> 00:02:40,267
If you tell me
everything you know,

35
00:02:41,367 --> 00:02:43,600
I'll talk to our lawyer.

36
00:02:44,700 --> 00:02:45,867
To get me out of here?

37
00:02:48,633 --> 00:02:51,200
You have to pay
for what you did to Jade.

38
00:02:51,333 --> 00:02:54,867
But you, as the prime suspect
in my father's death...

39
00:02:55,967 --> 00:02:57,300
I can help you with that.

40
00:02:57,433 --> 00:02:58,400
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

41
00:02:58,533 --> 00:03:01,300
[LEON] I'll testify myself.

42
00:03:02,100 --> 00:03:03,833
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

43
00:03:12,967 --> 00:03:15,733
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

44
00:03:15,867 --> 00:03:16,833
Okay.

45
00:03:18,033 --> 00:03:20,267
You were always with Dad.

46
00:03:21,033 --> 00:03:22,367
From the people around him,

47
00:03:23,400 --> 00:03:25,800
did you ever notice anyone
who seemed to hate him?

48
00:03:25,933 --> 00:03:27,233
An enemy?

49
00:03:30,133 --> 00:03:31,133
Absolutely.

50
00:03:31,267 --> 00:03:36,967
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

51
00:03:37,100 --> 00:03:38,367
Sir Mike.

52
00:03:39,967 --> 00:03:41,733
They got into a fight,
remember?

53
00:03:41,867 --> 00:03:42,967
[LEON] We already know that.

54
00:03:43,400 --> 00:03:46,800
What do you know that we don't?

55
00:03:50,200 --> 00:03:51,400
[SIGHS]

56
00:03:51,533 --> 00:03:54,200
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

57
00:03:54,367 --> 00:03:56,533
Leon, I can't think straight.

58
00:03:58,633 --> 00:04:00,833
But if you send in Frida...

59
00:04:02,267 --> 00:04:03,600
maybe I'll remember something.

60
00:04:07,933 --> 00:04:09,067
How's she doing?

61
00:04:09,200 --> 00:04:16,233
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

62
00:04:29,400 --> 00:04:31,200
- [LIGHT FOOTSTEPS]
- [WAVES LAPPING]

63
00:04:31,333 --> 00:04:34,600
Leon went to see Roi,
the former driver?

64
00:04:35,400 --> 00:04:36,900
What did they talk about?

65
00:04:37,033 --> 00:04:41,233
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

66
00:04:41,367 --> 00:04:42,833
But he didn't learn anything?

67
00:04:45,500 --> 00:04:48,867
He's still a wildcard,
so keep a close eye on him.

68
00:04:51,167 --> 00:04:52,267
[CELL PHONE BEEPS]

69
00:04:55,867 --> 00:04:57,833
[ANDY]
<i> Go ahead if you want, Leon.</i>

70
00:05:00,000 --> 00:05:01,467
<i> I'll catch you eventually.</i>

71
00:05:03,367 --> 00:05:04,567
Come on!

72
00:05:04,700 --> 00:05:06,733
[JADE] Wait a minute.
Where are you taking me?

73
00:05:06,867 --> 00:05:09,833
- Let's just keep walking.
- We're almost there.

74
00:05:09,967 --> 00:05:12,200
Okay. Are we close?

75
00:05:12,333 --> 00:05:14,133
- Yes.
- Really?

76
00:05:14,267 --> 00:05:16,733
- You can take it off now.
- Okay.

77
00:05:16,867 --> 00:05:19,267
Oh, you and your silly
little games.

78
00:05:20,867 --> 00:05:23,400
- Snow!
- Snow!

79
00:05:23,533 --> 00:05:27,633
- [KIDS CHEERING, GIGGLING]
- [SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

80
00:05:27,767 --> 00:05:28,800
Wow!

81
00:05:28,933 --> 00:05:29,867
[BOY] Come on!

82
00:05:30,000 --> 00:05:33,033
[ALL GIGGLING]

83
00:05:36,733 --> 00:05:39,267
[GIRL]
Look at all these bubbles!

84
00:05:39,400 --> 00:05:41,867
[KIDS GIGGLING]

85
00:05:42,000 --> 00:05:44,933
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

86
00:05:45,067 --> 00:05:48,200
I'm sorry, it's the only kind
of snow I can summon here.

87
00:05:48,333 --> 00:05:49,833
[SNOW MACHINE WHIRRING]

88
00:05:49,967 --> 00:05:51,033
Thank you.

89
00:05:52,467 --> 00:05:53,700
[BOY] Catch them!

90
00:06:00,267 --> 00:06:01,867
[CHUCKLING]

91
00:06:02,000 --> 00:06:03,367
It's beautiful!

92
00:06:03,500 --> 00:06:05,133
[SQUEALS] It's so beautiful!

93
00:06:05,267 --> 00:06:08,900
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

94
00:06:09,067 --> 00:06:10,500
[JADE] Whoa! Lots of snow!

95
00:06:10,633 --> 00:06:13,100
There's a lot of snow!

96
00:06:13,233 --> 00:06:14,167
[GIGGLES]

97
00:06:14,300 --> 00:06:15,800
Wow!

98
00:06:15,933 --> 00:06:18,567
[SQUEALING]

99
00:06:19,133 --> 00:06:20,800
Let's enjoy the snow!

100
00:06:20,933 --> 00:06:24,433
[JADE GIGGLING]

101
00:06:24,567 --> 00:06:31,600
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

102
00:06:46,267 --> 00:06:53,133
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

103
00:07:09,000 --> 00:07:10,033
Hang on.

104
00:07:10,167 --> 00:07:11,567
Wait for me.
Stay right there.

105
00:07:11,700 --> 00:07:13,100
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY]
Don't go anywhere.

106
00:07:13,233 --> 00:07:15,067
[WAVES LAPPING]

107
00:07:15,233 --> 00:07:16,500
[EDWARD] What are you doing?

108
00:07:17,233 --> 00:07:18,833
[JADE GIGGLES] Just wait!

109
00:07:18,967 --> 00:07:22,533
[STICK SCRAPING]

110
00:07:24,333 --> 00:07:25,500
[CHUCKLES]

111
00:07:32,933 --> 00:07:33,933
There!

112
00:07:35,400 --> 00:07:36,300
[EDWARD] What's that?

113
00:07:36,433 --> 00:07:39,267
[JADE] A big "Thank You."

114
00:07:39,400 --> 00:07:43,333
[GENTLE MUSIC PLAYING]

115
00:07:43,467 --> 00:07:45,633
For making it snow
in the Philippines?

116
00:07:46,933 --> 00:07:50,800
For reminding me that there
are many reasons to be happy.

117
00:07:51,467 --> 00:07:55,167
Even though I'm sad
that my dad is gone,

118
00:07:55,300 --> 00:07:56,800
even though my mom is
so far away,

119
00:07:56,933 --> 00:07:59,667
even though there's a lot
of problems at the hotel...

120
00:08:00,533 --> 00:08:02,867
There's still reason
to be happy.

121
00:08:03,333 --> 00:08:04,500
So...

122
00:08:05,100 --> 00:08:06,300
thank you!

123
00:08:06,433 --> 00:08:07,300
[GENTLE MUSIC CONTINUES]

124
00:08:07,433 --> 00:08:10,667
[BOTH CHUCKLING]

125
00:08:11,600 --> 00:08:13,233
Wait, I think it's
missing something.

126
00:08:13,367 --> 00:08:15,867
Really? What do you
mean something--

127
00:08:16,400 --> 00:08:17,767
- Hang on--
- Stand right here.

128
00:08:17,900 --> 00:08:18,867
Perfect.

129
00:08:19,000 --> 00:08:20,133
[CHUCKLES] Edward...

130
00:08:21,533 --> 00:08:22,833
Smile!

131
00:08:22,967 --> 00:08:23,833
Come on.

132
00:08:23,967 --> 00:08:25,733
- A big smile, okay?
- [GIGGLES]

133
00:08:25,867 --> 00:08:27,567
That's it. Three, two, one!

134
00:08:27,700 --> 00:08:28,867
- Like this?
- Bigger.

135
00:08:29,000 --> 00:08:29,933
- This?
- Great.

136
00:08:30,067 --> 00:08:30,933
[JADE CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

137
00:08:31,067 --> 00:08:33,033
- There we go!
- [CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKING]

138
00:08:33,167 --> 00:08:34,433
[JADE GIGGLING]

139
00:08:35,267 --> 00:08:38,367
Before the waves wash away
the biggest thanks

140
00:08:38,500 --> 00:08:39,800
I've ever gotten...

141
00:08:41,167 --> 00:08:43,167
[SHOUTS] You're welcome!

142
00:08:43,300 --> 00:08:46,600
[BOTH CHUCKLING]

143
00:08:46,733 --> 00:08:53,767
[GENTLE MUSIC CONTINUES]

144
00:09:07,233 --> 00:09:14,067
[GENTLE MUSIC CONTINUES]

145
00:09:18,367 --> 00:09:19,500
[WOMAN] Ma'am!

146
00:09:20,367 --> 00:09:22,300
Please help me!

147
00:09:22,433 --> 00:09:24,100
- [OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]
- [WOMAN CRYING]

148
00:09:24,233 --> 00:09:26,767
Help! Please help me!

149
00:09:26,900 --> 00:09:28,433
- Help me!
- What's going on?

150
00:09:28,600 --> 00:09:31,333
My Kulas! He's lost
somewhere in the sea!

151
00:09:31,467 --> 00:09:33,000
They couldn't find him. Maybe--

152
00:09:33,133 --> 00:09:34,567
Maybe his boat capsized!

153
00:09:34,700 --> 00:09:36,933
- Please help me!
- Mister Kulas...

154
00:09:37,067 --> 00:09:39,767
He's the father of one
of the kids I teach, Edward.

155
00:09:40,567 --> 00:09:41,933
- Take care of her.
- What?

156
00:09:42,067 --> 00:09:43,633
- I'll leave you to her.
- Edward!

157
00:09:43,767 --> 00:09:45,133
- Edward, where are you going?!
- Mister!

158
00:09:45,267 --> 00:09:48,067
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

159
00:09:48,200 --> 00:09:49,133
[EDWARD] Mister!

160
00:09:49,667 --> 00:09:51,000
I need your help!

161
00:09:51,900 --> 00:09:53,167
Let's head to the sea!

162
00:09:59,300 --> 00:10:01,033
Please help my husband!

163
00:10:01,200 --> 00:10:04,767
[SOBBING]

164
00:10:11,033 --> 00:10:12,067
Come.

165
00:10:13,933 --> 00:10:15,367
[PEOPLE CHATTERING]

166
00:10:16,733 --> 00:10:23,767
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

167
00:10:38,733 --> 00:10:45,767
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

168
00:10:50,167 --> 00:10:51,867
Okay, I'm coming back there.

169
00:10:52,000 --> 00:10:53,433
I'll just buy something.

170
00:11:00,733 --> 00:11:07,767
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

171
00:11:09,000 --> 00:11:10,867
Cheska, can you not?

172
00:11:12,300 --> 00:11:14,267
Girl, this is important.

173
00:11:14,867 --> 00:11:17,633
We don't know if
we can use this as evidence.

174
00:11:17,767 --> 00:11:19,767
- Just be careful, okay?
- I will.

175
00:11:19,900 --> 00:11:20,933
I'll be careful.

176
00:11:22,700 --> 00:11:23,933
Come, let's keep moving.

177
00:11:24,633 --> 00:11:26,100
Move slowly.

178
00:11:26,700 --> 00:11:28,200
[CHESKA COUGHING]

179
00:11:28,333 --> 00:11:35,167
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

180
00:11:50,333 --> 00:11:57,167
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

181
00:12:04,333 --> 00:12:06,767
He might see your hair tie.

182
00:12:12,333 --> 00:12:16,067
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

183
00:12:16,233 --> 00:12:17,500
Subject moving, let's get going!

184
00:12:17,633 --> 00:12:19,033
- Move! Let's go!
- Be careful.

185
00:12:22,800 --> 00:12:24,167
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

186
00:12:24,300 --> 00:12:27,233
[SARI] Sir, Sir Martin has
been looking for you.

187
00:12:27,367 --> 00:12:28,500
Okay.

188
00:12:28,633 --> 00:12:31,933
Sir, I'll let you know now
so you won't get shocked.

189
00:12:40,467 --> 00:12:41,533
What is it?

190
00:12:42,367 --> 00:12:43,300
[GASPS]

191
00:12:43,433 --> 00:12:45,267
You caught me off-guard, sir.

192
00:12:45,800 --> 00:12:46,967
- Sari?
- Uh.

193
00:12:47,100 --> 00:12:48,267
I-I mean...

194
00:12:48,433 --> 00:12:51,567
Just be ready because I think
Miss Luna and Sir Martin's

195
00:12:51,700 --> 00:12:53,367
conversation didn't end well.

196
00:12:53,500 --> 00:12:54,733
[MARTIN] Leon.

197
00:12:57,500 --> 00:12:59,200
Luna refused.

198
00:13:01,000 --> 00:13:01,667
[SIGHS DEEPLY]

199
00:13:01,800 --> 00:13:03,267
Can you excuse us first?

200
00:13:03,400 --> 00:13:07,300
[LEON BREATHES DEEPLY]

201
00:13:07,433 --> 00:13:14,267
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

202
00:13:19,500 --> 00:13:26,533
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

203
00:13:41,533 --> 00:13:45,333
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

204
00:13:45,467 --> 00:13:46,567
[CHESKA] Hurry up!

205
00:13:46,700 --> 00:13:49,233
[JUSTIN] Hey! Wait!
Wait a second!

206
00:13:49,367 --> 00:13:50,800
[CHESKA] Why should we wait?
What are you doing?

207
00:13:50,933 --> 00:13:53,300
The kidnapper might escape,
you know?

208
00:13:53,433 --> 00:13:54,900
Just go back.

209
00:13:55,067 --> 00:13:57,600
Justin, we're this close already
and you're sending us back now?

210
00:13:57,733 --> 00:13:58,800
That's the point!

211
00:13:58,933 --> 00:14:00,467
We're getting closer to danger.

212
00:14:00,600 --> 00:14:01,767
[TRIXIE SCOFFS]

213
00:14:01,900 --> 00:14:03,267
Are you scared, Justin?

214
00:14:03,400 --> 00:14:05,867
If you're scared,
then let's go alone, Cheska.

215
00:14:06,000 --> 00:14:06,867
Me?

216
00:14:07,000 --> 00:14:08,000
Scared?

217
00:14:08,133 --> 00:14:09,367
No.

218
00:14:09,500 --> 00:14:10,933
I'm giving you a way out.

219
00:14:11,067 --> 00:14:11,900
One last time.

220
00:14:12,033 --> 00:14:13,200
[CHESKA] You blabber
too much, Justin!

221
00:14:13,333 --> 00:14:15,067
We're past the point of
no return! Let's move!

222
00:14:15,200 --> 00:14:18,233
- Oh my gosh, Justin! Hurry up!
- [JUSTIN MUMBLES]

223
00:14:18,367 --> 00:14:19,433
[CHESKA] You talk too much!

224
00:14:19,567 --> 00:14:20,967
- [JUSTIN HISSES]
- [CHESKA] Hurry up!

225
00:14:22,967 --> 00:14:25,100
[LEON] Let's decide
by voting again.

226
00:14:25,233 --> 00:14:27,700
Uncle Andy can't be
a partner nor an investor

227
00:14:27,833 --> 00:14:30,200
if the majority of us
don't agree with it.

228
00:14:30,367 --> 00:14:31,133
[MARTIN] Bro.

229
00:14:31,267 --> 00:14:34,433
Bro, this time I will
vote with you.

230
00:14:34,567 --> 00:14:35,733
I will vote for your
Uncle Ronald.

231
00:14:35,867 --> 00:14:36,967
I'll make sure of it.

232
00:14:37,100 --> 00:14:39,333
Uncle Andy should just
never get in here.

233
00:14:39,467 --> 00:14:40,667
Tell me,

234
00:14:40,800 --> 00:14:43,200
what's your problem
with Uncle Andy?

235
00:14:43,333 --> 00:14:45,800
[INHALES SHARPLY]
I can't tell you yet.

236
00:14:45,933 --> 00:14:49,267
But I'm certain that
we can't trust him.

237
00:14:49,400 --> 00:14:50,367
Why?

238
00:14:50,500 --> 00:14:52,400
- What did he do?
- Not now, bro.

239
00:14:52,533 --> 00:14:54,200
I'm telling you this
as your friend.

240
00:14:54,333 --> 00:14:55,967
For your sake.

241
00:14:56,100 --> 00:14:57,200
For the hotel.

242
00:14:57,333 --> 00:14:58,600
For all of us!

243
00:14:58,733 --> 00:15:00,933
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

244
00:15:01,100 --> 00:15:02,467
Martin.

245
00:15:02,600 --> 00:15:04,667
I need your help.

246
00:15:05,467 --> 00:15:08,267
Andy can't be here in the hotel.

247
00:15:08,400 --> 00:15:10,133
By any means!

248
00:15:10,267 --> 00:15:12,533
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

249
00:15:12,667 --> 00:15:14,900
[SIGHS] Okay, okay.

250
00:15:16,000 --> 00:15:17,067
Okay.

251
00:15:23,467 --> 00:15:26,000
[GRASS RUSTLING]

252
00:15:27,533 --> 00:15:28,567
[CAR DOOR OPENS]

253
00:15:31,167 --> 00:15:32,233
[CAR DOOR CLOSES]

254
00:15:32,367 --> 00:15:39,400
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

255
00:15:39,967 --> 00:15:41,400
Is that it?

256
00:15:41,533 --> 00:15:44,233
Is that the car they used
to abduct Juan?

257
00:15:44,367 --> 00:15:46,267
Guys, it seems like it is.

258
00:15:54,367 --> 00:15:58,700
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

259
00:15:58,833 --> 00:16:00,800
[CHESKA] All right, they really
brought Juan here.

260
00:16:02,000 --> 00:16:03,300
[JUSTIN] We're not sure
about that.

261
00:16:03,433 --> 00:16:05,233
What if that's the safehouse
for more of their men?

262
00:16:05,367 --> 00:16:11,767
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

263
00:16:11,933 --> 00:16:13,267
[CHESKA] Hey.

264
00:16:15,133 --> 00:16:16,367
You act like you know
a lot about this.

265
00:16:16,500 --> 00:16:19,300
Have you kidnapped
people before too?

266
00:16:19,433 --> 00:16:20,567
[JUSTIN] It's none
of your business.

267
00:16:26,967 --> 00:16:33,800
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

268
00:16:43,533 --> 00:16:45,200
So what's next?
What are we going to do now?

269
00:16:45,333 --> 00:16:47,500
Next? We're going home now!

270
00:16:47,633 --> 00:16:48,700
[TRIXIE] What?!

271
00:16:49,933 --> 00:16:53,900
[JUSTIN] Would you rather go
home or get caught here instead?

272
00:16:54,033 --> 00:16:55,833
- Let's go home.
- Yeah, let's get moving.

273
00:16:58,633 --> 00:17:00,167
- Please drink slowly.
- [EXHALES SHARPLY]

274
00:17:01,300 --> 00:17:03,967
My worries aren't going away.

275
00:17:04,100 --> 00:17:05,567
What if Kulas drowned?

276
00:17:05,700 --> 00:17:07,033
Miss, don't say that.

277
00:17:07,167 --> 00:17:09,000
As long as we haven't
heard any news,

278
00:17:09,133 --> 00:17:10,967
let's not lose hope, okay?

279
00:17:11,100 --> 00:17:13,700
Jade, where's my father?

280
00:17:13,833 --> 00:17:15,500
Calm down. Just relax.

281
00:17:18,200 --> 00:17:19,833
- [WHIMPERING]
- The boat's incoming.

282
00:17:19,967 --> 00:17:21,067
Let's just relax.

283
00:17:21,200 --> 00:17:23,567
I'm sure they have
good news, okay?

284
00:17:23,700 --> 00:17:24,600
[WHIMPERING]

285
00:17:24,733 --> 00:17:29,000
[BOAT ENGINE WHIRRING]

286
00:17:29,133 --> 00:17:31,967
The boat's here now.

287
00:17:32,100 --> 00:17:33,933
[KULAS'S WIFE]
Oh, there's Kulas!

288
00:17:34,067 --> 00:17:37,400
Your father's there! He's safe!

289
00:17:37,533 --> 00:17:39,400
Kulas!

290
00:17:39,533 --> 00:17:42,100
- [KULAS'S SON] Father!
- [KULAS'S WIFE CRYING]

291
00:17:42,233 --> 00:17:43,600
Kulas!

292
00:17:43,733 --> 00:17:46,233
Your father's back!
Thank you, sir.

293
00:17:46,367 --> 00:17:48,233
Thank you so much!

294
00:17:48,400 --> 00:17:50,733
Your father's safe!

295
00:17:50,867 --> 00:17:52,233
[KULAS'S SON]
Daddy, are you all right?

296
00:17:52,367 --> 00:17:53,333
Yes, I am, son.

297
00:17:53,467 --> 00:17:55,900
- That's good to hear.
- Sir Edward...

298
00:17:56,033 --> 00:17:57,833
I just want to thank you again.

299
00:17:59,000 --> 00:18:01,133
[KULAS] I owe you my life.

300
00:18:01,267 --> 00:18:03,667
[KULAS'S WIFE]
Thank you so much, sir.

301
00:18:03,800 --> 00:18:07,067
[KULAS'S WIFE CRYING]

302
00:18:07,200 --> 00:18:08,967
Thank you so much.

303
00:18:09,100 --> 00:18:10,833
[KULAS'S SON CRYING]
Thank you, sir.

304
00:18:10,967 --> 00:18:12,267
Thank you, sir.

305
00:18:12,400 --> 00:18:15,900
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

306
00:18:16,033 --> 00:18:17,200
[KULAS'S WIFE] Thank you, sir.

307
00:18:21,133 --> 00:18:22,200
Sir Edward!

308
00:18:22,367 --> 00:18:24,367
I just want to say
thank you again.

309
00:18:27,000 --> 00:18:28,867
I owe you my life.

310
00:18:32,733 --> 00:18:35,467
If only you saw our situation
earlier, Miss Jade.

311
00:18:35,600 --> 00:18:40,600
I was floating for so long
after my boat capsized.

312
00:18:40,733 --> 00:18:43,267
It reached a point when
I couldn't take it anymore.

313
00:18:43,400 --> 00:18:46,267
Just as I was about to sink,

314
00:18:46,400 --> 00:18:48,300
Sir Edward suddenly arrived.

315
00:18:48,433 --> 00:18:51,067
He saw me and
he dove into the ocean

316
00:18:51,200 --> 00:18:52,833
just to save me.

317
00:18:52,967 --> 00:18:57,067
Because the current
underwater was so strong...

318
00:18:57,233 --> 00:19:00,200
he got scraped by the corals.

319
00:19:00,333 --> 00:19:03,000
[GENTLE MUSIC PLAYING]

320
00:19:03,133 --> 00:19:05,300
[KULAS] Thank you again,
Sir Edward.

321
00:19:06,667 --> 00:19:09,700
Kulas, anyone would do the same.

322
00:19:09,833 --> 00:19:11,300
But you're welcome.

323
00:19:18,100 --> 00:19:23,267
[GENTLE MUSIC FADING]

324
00:19:24,367 --> 00:19:28,033
[LUNA SOBBING] Peter!

325
00:19:28,200 --> 00:19:30,300
<i> Help!</i>

326
00:19:30,433 --> 00:19:34,867
<i>Oh my, the girl!
Help us!</i>

327
00:19:35,000 --> 00:19:37,833
[SCREAMING] Help us!

328
00:19:37,967 --> 00:19:40,233
[SOBBING]

329
00:19:40,367 --> 00:19:43,900
<i> Peter!</i>

330
00:19:44,033 --> 00:19:47,700
<i> Help! Please help us!</i>

331
00:19:47,833 --> 00:19:48,867
[GIRL] Miss?

332
00:19:56,267 --> 00:20:03,267
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

333
00:20:09,133 --> 00:20:11,633
[SNIFFLES]

334
00:20:14,967 --> 00:20:16,033
Hello.

335
00:20:18,967 --> 00:20:20,900
I'm Luna.

336
00:20:21,033 --> 00:20:25,267
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

337
00:20:25,400 --> 00:20:26,567
[BREATHES HEAVILY]

338
00:20:26,700 --> 00:20:28,467
I'm sorry.

339
00:20:29,833 --> 00:20:31,867
I'm sorry.

340
00:20:40,433 --> 00:20:45,600
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

341
00:20:45,733 --> 00:20:47,067
I'm sorry.

342
00:20:47,200 --> 00:20:49,033
[SNIFFLES] I'm sorry.

343
00:21:00,600 --> 00:21:07,633
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

344
00:21:13,300 --> 00:21:14,300
I really thought

345
00:21:15,433 --> 00:21:16,967
I was going to lose my child.

346
00:21:19,633 --> 00:21:22,833
We nearly cursed you
and your boyfriend's name,

347
00:21:22,967 --> 00:21:24,567
the people who shot my daughter,

348
00:21:25,633 --> 00:21:28,067
because we were so mad at you.

349
00:21:30,967 --> 00:21:31,933
[SNIFFLES]

350
00:21:33,700 --> 00:21:34,867
I'm sorry.

351
00:21:37,200 --> 00:21:38,367
I'm really sorry.

352
00:21:38,500 --> 00:21:39,600
[SNIFFLES]

353
00:21:40,900 --> 00:21:42,733
You didn't want that
to happen, right?

354
00:21:42,900 --> 00:21:44,567
[GENTLE MUSIC PLAYING]

355
00:21:44,700 --> 00:21:46,367
And that gun wasn't yours.

356
00:21:51,833 --> 00:21:53,200
It was all an accident.

357
00:21:54,900 --> 00:21:56,333
And it is a miracle

358
00:21:57,033 --> 00:21:59,333
that our child is still alive.

359
00:22:02,267 --> 00:22:03,300
That's why...

360
00:22:04,600 --> 00:22:08,167
we chose not to live in anger.

361
00:22:13,900 --> 00:22:15,967
We've already
forgiven you, Luna.

362
00:22:18,433 --> 00:22:19,300
Hopefully...

363
00:22:20,667 --> 00:22:23,133
you can forgive yourself
as well.

364
00:22:23,267 --> 00:22:30,033
[GENTLE MUSIC CONTINUES]

365
00:22:44,933 --> 00:22:50,433
[GENTLE MUSIC CONTINUES]

366
00:22:50,600 --> 00:22:51,900
[LUNA]
<i> I'll come home late, Leon.</i>

367
00:22:52,033 --> 00:22:53,833
<i> We traveled to Manila.</i>

368
00:22:53,967 --> 00:22:55,533
<i>Don't worry,
I have someone with me.</i>

369
00:22:55,667 --> 00:23:02,333
- [FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]
- [WAVES CRASHING]

370
00:23:03,800 --> 00:23:05,067
[CLATTERS]

371
00:23:06,333 --> 00:23:09,900
[FOREBODING MUSIC PLAYING]

372
00:23:10,033 --> 00:23:11,967
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

373
00:23:12,100 --> 00:23:12,800
Who are you?

374
00:23:12,933 --> 00:23:18,033
[MUSIC TURNS TENSE]

375
00:23:18,167 --> 00:23:19,900
- [BAT CLANKS]
- [LEON GRUNTING] Argh!

376
00:23:20,033 --> 00:23:21,800
- [PHONE THUDS]
- [FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

377
00:23:21,967 --> 00:23:23,467
- [BLOW LANDS]
- [LEON GROANS]

378
00:23:23,600 --> 00:23:24,400
- [KICK LANDS]
- [MAN GRUNTS]

379
00:23:24,533 --> 00:23:25,400
[BODY THUDS]

380
00:23:25,533 --> 00:23:27,467
[BLOWS LAND]

381
00:23:27,600 --> 00:23:29,400
Hey!

382
00:23:29,533 --> 00:23:31,900
[BLOWS LAND]

383
00:23:32,033 --> 00:23:33,667
- [KICK LANDS]
- [MAN GROANS] Agh!

384
00:23:33,800 --> 00:23:35,100
- [BLOW LANDS]
- [MAN GROANS] Agh!

385
00:23:35,233 --> 00:23:36,033
[BODY THUDS]

386
00:23:36,167 --> 00:23:38,067
- [BLOWS LANDING]
- [MAN GROANING] Agh!

387
00:23:38,200 --> 00:23:40,433
- [BLOW LANDS]
- [LEON GROANS] Agh!

388
00:23:40,567 --> 00:23:44,733
- [BLOWS LAND]
- [KICKS LAND]

389
00:23:44,867 --> 00:23:50,800
- [BAT CLANKS]
- [BLOWS, KICKS LAND]

390
00:23:54,500 --> 00:23:55,467
It's not here!

391
00:24:00,633 --> 00:24:02,467
- [MAN 1] What?
- This is not it.

392
00:24:02,600 --> 00:24:03,767
Open the door. Hurry!

393
00:24:04,800 --> 00:24:06,167
[CAR DOORS OPEN]

394
00:24:07,900 --> 00:24:11,267
[OBJECTS THUDDING]

395
00:24:11,400 --> 00:24:14,033
[LEON GROANING]

396
00:24:14,167 --> 00:24:15,400
[COUGHING]

397
00:24:18,300 --> 00:24:19,267
It's not here!

398
00:24:21,667 --> 00:24:24,300
When I find out who sent you...

399
00:24:26,433 --> 00:24:28,133
I'll make you pay.

400
00:24:29,467 --> 00:24:30,400
Let's go! Hurry up!

401
00:24:31,133 --> 00:24:34,967
[FOOTSTEPS RETREATING]

402
00:24:36,367 --> 00:24:39,033
[LEON BREATHING SHARPLY]

403
00:24:39,167 --> 00:24:46,100
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

404
00:24:49,133 --> 00:24:51,267
<i>- Dad? What's up with Leon?
- Hey.</i>

405
00:24:51,400 --> 00:24:53,900
<i>Luna might be the only one
who wants to partner with us.</i>

406
00:24:54,033 --> 00:24:56,200
<i>All the more reason
for you to get Jade.</i>

407
00:24:56,333 --> 00:24:58,767
<i>Is Edward
your sister's boyfriend?</i>

408
00:24:58,900 --> 00:25:00,400
<i> I'm not sure.</i>

409
00:25:00,533 --> 00:25:02,933
<i>You have no idea what
your smile does to me.</i>

410
00:25:05,000 --> 00:25:06,500
<i> They were really close, bro.</i>

411
00:25:08,767 --> 00:25:10,900
<i> They almost kissed.</i>

412
00:25:11,033 --> 00:25:12,300
<i> Let's just stay here.</i>

413
00:25:13,700 --> 00:25:15,367
<i> Let's not go back.</i>
